This Resource describes the colour using chroma conventions.
"hue" is the hue angle, it is an integer value as defined by the
CIECAM02 model definition (see reference [CIE CIE159:2004]). The
Property "saturation" is an integer value as defined by the CIECAM02
model definition (see reference [CIE CIE159:2004]). The Property
"maximumsaturation" is the upper bound on the saturation supported by
the Device. If not present the maximum value for "saturation" is
32767. The Property "csc" is the colour space coordinates in CIE
colour space. The first item in the array is the X coordinate. The
second item in the array is the Y coordinate. The Property "nct" is
the Mired colour temperature. The Resource provides the colour using
The hue angle as defined by the CIECAM02 model definition.
The saturation as defined by the CIECAM02 model definition.
The maximum supported value of "saturation" for this Device.
The X and Y coordinates of the colour in CIE colour space
